{{Page version|42.17.0}}
'''Importing assets''' is a process needed to directly edit existing game assets to readapt them, or to use them in external projects such as [[Rendering|renders]] in Blender. Due to most model and animation assets using DirectX, an outdated format, most 3D modeling software do not support it natively. Tools exist and were made specifically for Project Zomboid in some cases to allow you to import DirectX files into softwares like [[Wikipedia:Blender|Blender]].

{| class="wikitable theme-blue sortable" style="text-align: center;
|+ style="white-space:nowrap" | Model and animation import tools
|-
! Tool !! Description !! Model import !! Animation import !! Last updated
